/svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526038\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526038\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 17, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bgr1665702681402.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bgr1665702681402.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bgr1665702681402.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bgr1665702681402\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      trigger formatToDbms\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">System trigger for encrypting data in a field when writing to the database. Use when implementing secure systems.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bgr1665702681402__section_w463ab1b7b1_w464ab1b7_w465ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bgr1665702681402__table_d14249e1_d14250e1_d14251e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Declaration:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">trigger formatToDbms</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Applies to:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lym1665702585074.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lym1665702585074.html\" title=\"A Field is a Development Object that represents a unit of data in an Entity. This could represent a column in a DBMS table or data that is not stored in the database, such as a derived field or a user interface control. Its associated properties define the way it is stored, its GUI representation, and default behavior.\">Field</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activation:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activated when data for the field is written to the database.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Default behavior:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n None\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Behavior upon completion:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n None\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bgr1665702681402__section_w466ab1b7b3_w467ab1b7_w468ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d234346e129\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bgr1665702681402__p_d116231e1_d116232e1_d116233e1\">The formatToDbms and formatFromDbms triggers enable you to implement secure systems. These triggers must provide round trip (inverse) results; that is, the source data in the database at the start of the process should be the same as the result after decryption and encryption.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bgr1665702681402__p_d116234e1_d116235e1_d116236e1\">You can also use this trigger to convert an unsupported DBMS data type into one that Uniface can handle.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bgr1665702681402__p_d116237e1_d116238e1_d116239e1\">Encryption can be done in either ProcScript or 3GL. In ProcScript, you can use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$encode</span> to encrypt data and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$decode</span> to decrypt data. For 3GL-based encryption, you can write a 3GL service for decryption and encryption and use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> statement to activate it.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bgr1665702681402__section_w469ab1b7b5_w470ab1b7_w471ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d234346e153\">\n                       \n Trigger Activation\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bgr1665702681402__p_d116243e1_d116244e1_d116245e1\">When writing data to the database, the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">write</span> statement in the write (or writeUp) trigger for the entity activates the formatToDbms trigger for each field in the entity for which the formatToDbms trigger contains ProcScript.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bgr1665702681402__p_d116246e1_d116247e1_d116248e1\">If the formatFromDbms trigger for the field contains ProcScript, it is also activated by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">write</span> statement immediately after firing the formatToDbms trigger, to synchronize internal data representation.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rkb1689666715569.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$encode</a><p>Encrypt data, sign messages with digital signatures, or convert data from one encoding scheme to another.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ojm1665702681473.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger formatFromDbms</a><p>System trigger for decrypting data for a field when reading from the database. Use when implementing secure systems.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rjr1665703129938.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger write</a><p>System trigger that handles processing when a new or modified occurrence is written to the database.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rog1665702561386.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger writeUp</a><p>System trigger that handles processing when a new or modified occurrence of an Up entity must be written to the database.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/boe1665702681628.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Call-Out From formatToDbms and formatFromDbms Triggers</a><p>You can encrypt and decrypt data that is stored and retrieved from the database using the formatToDbms and formatFromDbms triggers of a field.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526038\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526038\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "trigger formatToDbms Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 trigger formatToDbms System trigger for encrypting data in a field when writing to the database. Use when implementing secure systems. Declaration: trigger formatToDbms Applies to: Field Activation: Activated when data for the field is written to the database. Default behavior: None Behavior upon completion: None Description The formatToDbms and formatFromDbms triggers enable you to implement secure systems. These triggers must provide round trip (inverse) results; that is, the source data in the database at the start of the process should be the same as the result after decryption and encryption. You can also use this trigger to convert an unsupported DBMS data type into one that Uniface can handle. Encryption can be done in either ProcScript or 3GL. In ProcScript, you can use $encode to encrypt data and $decode to decrypt data. For 3GL-based encryption, you can write a 3GL service for decryption and encryption and use the activate statement to activate it. Trigger Activation When writing data to the database, the write statement in the write (or writeUp) trigger for the entity activates the formatToDbms trigger for each field in the entity for which the formatToDbms trigger contains ProcScript. If the formatFromDbms trigger for the field contains ProcScript, it is also activated by the write statement immediately after firing the formatToDbms trigger, to synchronize internal data representation. Related Links $encode Encrypt data, sign messages with digital signatures, or convert data from one encoding scheme to another. trigger formatFromDbms System trigger for decrypting data for a field when reading from the database. Use when implementing secure systems. trigger write System trigger that handles processing when a new or modified occurrence is written to the database. trigger writeUp System trigger that handles processing when a new or modified occurrence of an Up entity must be written to the database. Call-Out From formatToDbms and formatFromDbms Triggers You can encrypt and decrypt data that is stored and retrieved from the database using the formatToDbms and formatFromDbms triggers of a field. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}